Description: Fix CVE-2025-69223 (GHSA-6mq8-rvhq-8wgg) zip-bomb DoS in aiohttp HTTP body decompression.
 The aiohttp HTTP parser auto_decompress feature did not bound output size, allowing a small
 compressed payload (zlib/gzip/brotli) to expand to gigabytes and exhaust host memory (CWE-409).
 Upstream fix introduces DEFAULT_MAX_DECOMPRESS_SIZE = 32 MiB and raises DecompressSizeError
 when the cap is exceeded. See upstream commit 2b920c39 and PR #11898/#11918.
 .
 Backport adapted for aiohttp 3.8.6 - re-implemented because compression_utils.py does not exist
 in this branch. In 3.8.6 the decompression logic lives inline in aiohttp/http_parser.py
 (DeflateBuffer with a local BrotliDecoder + raw zlib.decompressobj()) and in
 aiohttp/multipart.py (BodyPartReader._decode_content using zlib.decompress). ZSTD support is
 absent from 3.8.6 so the upstream HAS_ZSTD branch is omitted. BodyPartReader.decode() is kept
 sync (the upstream patch makes it async, which is a breaking change) - the size cap is applied
 synchronously instead. Upstream regression tests are not included because they import from
 compression_utils which does not exist on this branch.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/aio-libs/aiohttp/commit/2b920c39002cee0ec5b402581779bbaaf7c9138a
