Description: Fix CVE-2025-69226 path traversal in static file resource
 The path normalization logic for static files (intended to prevent path
 traversal) could be exploited by an attacker to determine whether absolute
 path components exist on the server. This patch adds os.path.normpath
 normalization at resolve() time so that a URL like /static/../../etc/passwd
 no longer matches the static prefix at all (returns 404), and also drops
 the now-redundant Path.anchor HTTPForbidden(403) guard in _handle().
 Backported from upstream commit f2a86fd5ac0383000d1715afddfa704413f0711e
 (aiohttp 3.13.3) to 3.8.6. The 3.8.6 patch is a delta on top of the earlier
 local static-resource patches in this hook, so it preserves the existing
 unresolved_path normalization logic and applies to request.rel_url.raw_path
 because yarl.URL.path_safe does not exist in the 3.8 era.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/aio-libs/aiohttp/commit/f2a86fd5ac0383000d1715afddfa704413f0711e
Author: Sam Bull <git@sambull.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-12

