performed via Python's stdlib http.cookies.SimpleCookie in
aiohttp/web_request.py, which silently drops invalid cookie names without
any logging. So the specific log-flood vector described by CVE-2025-69230
is structurally absent on this branch.

This is a defensive backport: it rewrites BaseRequest.cookies in
aiohttp/web_request.py so that any cookie chunks dropped by SimpleCookie
are aggregated and reported via a single DEBUG-level record on
internal_logger ("aiohttp.internal"). This mirrors the upstream fix
shape, so any future patch (or downstream change) that reintroduces
per-cookie logging cannot regress into a log-flood DoS, and it gives
operators a single, optional, throttled signal when invalid cookies are
present in a request. A regression test asserts that 3000 invalid cookie
names in a single Cookie header produce at most one DEBUG record.

