+    assert protocol._reading_paused is False

Description: Fix CVE-2026-22815 - Limit max headers to prevent uncapped memory usage
 Insufficient restrictions in header handling could cause uncapped memory
 usage. An application could cause memory exhaustion when receiving an
 attacker-controlled request or response. This minimal backport reduces the
 default max_headers from 32768 to 128 (matching upstream 3.13.4) and adds
 an explicit per-request header-count enforcement check in both the Python
 and Cython HTTP parsers, raising BadHttpMessage("Too many headers received")
 when the limit is exceeded. Backported from aio-libs/aiohttp commit
 0c2e9da51126238a421568eb7c5b53e5b5d17b36 with adaptation for v3.8.6 (the
 LineTooLong signature change, max_field_size accounting overhaul, trailer
 enforcement, and client.py/client_proto.py threading were intentionally
 omitted to keep the backport focused on the core CVE control surface).
 Tests backported: test_max_headers_exceeded, test_max_headers_under_limit,
 and test_max_headers_default_changed cover both the Python and C parsers.
 Upstream trailer-count tests omitted because trailer enforcement is not
 included in this backport.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/aio-libs/aiohttp/commit/0c2e9da51126238a421568eb7c5b53e5b5d17b36
Author: Sam Bull <git@sambull.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-08

