Description: Fix CVE-2026-34517 - check multipart max_size during iteration
 aiohttp's Request.post() previously read non-file multipart form fields entirely
 into memory via `await field.read(decode=True)` before enforcing client_max_size,
 allowing a remote attacker to force significant temporary memory allocation by
 sending a multipart request with an oversized non-file field. The size check
 happened only after the full field was buffered, enabling memory-based denial
 of service even though the request was ultimately rejected with HTTP 413.
 .
