Description: Fix CVE-2026-34516 - enforce multipart part header limits
 Multipart form parsing did not apply the server max_field_size and max_headers
 limits when reading headers for each MIME part, allowing attackers to send
 oversized or excessively numerous part headers and exhaust memory. This backport
 threads RequestHandler limits into MultipartReader, caps readline length during
 part header parsing, and raises BadHttpMessage/LineTooLong when limits are exceeded.
 StreamReader.readline/readuntil gain an optional max_size parameter (raising
 LineTooLong instead of ValueError) so the same limits can be enforced consistently.
 .
 Adapted for aiohttp 3.8.6 on top of prior local backports (multipart reader
 __init__ includes boundary/_mimetype validation from CVE-2024-30251 and related
 hooks; test import layout differs from pristine 3.8.6). Previous patch context
 targeted the unmodified upstream MultipartReader constructor and failed to apply.
